analysis.Summary: Vue 3 single-file component that renders an SVG ‘community’ icon with a configurable fill color.
analysis.Purpose: Provides a reusable icon component for the ‘community’ symbol, accepting a fill prop to adapt to different themes or contexts.

Components.name: IconCommunity
responsibilities: Render an SVG element of fixed dimensions (56×56).
Draw the community icon shape via a <path> element.
Accept a `fill` prop to dynamically set the path’s fill color.

Functions.name: defineProps
Functions.purpose: Define reactive props for the component in `<script setup>`.

Notes: No dedicated <style> block; styling is driven via the `fill` prop and CSS variables.
Uses `<script setup>` syntax, so no explicit export default.
SVG is hardcoded; there are no slots or additional customization beyond fill color.
Component is likely part of an icon library under modules/icons/entities.
